1.30	Gurdwara_Handi_Sahib	Gurdwara Handi Sahib	Gurdwara Handi Sahib is situated in Danapur is a cantonment station, 20 km west of old Patna City. Guru Tegh Bahadur had returned to Punjab in April 1670 leaving his family behind at Patna. The family after leaving Patna Sahib made their first halt here. An old lady named Mai Pardhani served a kettleful (handi) of khichari to them after which the shrine subsequently built here was named as Handiwali Sangat, which is now called Gurdwara handi Sahib.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/83/Bihar_locator_map.svg/240px-Bihar_locator_map.svg.png
